    <title ixia_locid="1" class="- topic/title ">Managing Physical Volumes</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="2" class="- topic/shortdesc ">You can add, delete, and review physical volumes on a compute
        host.</shortdesc>
    <prolog class="- topic/prolog ">
        <author ixia_locid="3" class="- topic/author ">Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
        <context id="context_N1001F_N1001C_N10001" ixia_locid="4" class="- topic/section task/context ">
            <p ixia_locid="6" class="- topic/p ">Physical volumes provide storage using local disks. You can use the
                web administration or the CLI to manage them. For web administration interface
                instructions, see <xref href="jow1426183480976.xml" ixia_locid="34" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
            <p ixia_locid="45" class="- topic/p ">As each physical volume is created, it is added to an existing local volume
                group.</p>
        </context>
        <prereq id="prereq_N1002D_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="8" class="- topic/section task/prereq ">
            <p ixia_locid="9" class="- topic/p ">Before you can modify the settings for a host, you must lock the host: </p>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="10" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="11" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="12" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">host-lock <varname ixia_locid="13" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">hostname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p ixia_locid="35" class="- topic/p ">Before you can add a physical volume, a local volume group must exist on the host. To
                create one, see <xref href="jow1426181291481.xml" ixia_locid="36" class="- topic/xref "/></p>
        </prereq>
        <context id="context_N10042_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="14" class="- topic/section task/context ">
            <p ixia_locid="15" class="- topic/p ">The following CLI commands are available for managing physical volumes.</p>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="16" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="17" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="18" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">host-pv-add <varname ixia_locid="19" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">hostname</varname> <varname ixia_locid="37" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">groupname</varname> <varname ixia_locid="20" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">disk_uuid</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p ixia_locid="38" class="- topic/p ">where <nameliteral ixia_locid="39" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">groupname</nameliteral> is the name of the local volume group to
                which the physical volume is added.</p>
            <note id="note_N1007A_N1004F_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="40" class="- topic/note ">
                <p ixia_locid="41" class="- topic/p ">The only valid <nameliteral ixia_locid="42" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">groupname</nameliteral> is
                        <nameliteral ixia_locid="43" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">nova-local</nameliteral>.</p>
            </note>
            <p ixia_locid="46" class="- topic/p ">When <nameliteral ixia_locid="47" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b wr-sw-d/nameliteral ">disk_uuid</nameliteral> indicates
                the root disk, the physical volume uses a system-designated partition on the root
                disk. For any other disk, the physical volume uses the entire disk.</p>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="21" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="22" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="23" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">host-pv-delete <varname ixia_locid="24" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">hostname</varname> <varname ixia_locid="44" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">nova-local</varname> <varname ixia_locid="25" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">disk_uuid</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="26" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="27" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="28" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">host-pv-list <varname ixia_locid="29" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">hostname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="30" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock "><systemoutput ixia_locid="31" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/systemoutput ">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="32" class="+ topic/ph sw-d/userinput ">host-pv-show <varname ixia_locid="33" class="+ topic/keyword sw-d/varname ">hostname</varname></userinput></codeblock>
        </context>
        <postreq id="postreq_N100E8_N1001F_N10001" ixia_locid="49" class="- topic/section task/postreq ">
            <p ixia_locid="50" class="- topic/p ">To configure VMs to use local storage, see <xref href="jow1426181040008.xml" ixia_locid="51" class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
        </postreq>
    </taskbody>
